items.text:
Volunteers Wanted - Liverpool Mystery Event

CAJ Productions is looking for 2 more reliable volunteers to help with a one-off mystery stunt in Liverpool City Centre on Saturday 20th September 2025.

It's part of a brand-new UK theatre tour coming in 2026, and this will be one of our headline public marketing stunts. 

The role is simple, but really important:

. Filming the event on a phone (1 person required)

. Guarding the event (managing livestream and any crowd that may form)

What you'll get:

. Travel covered

. Be part of an unusual, exciting event that's going to get a lot of attention

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

items.text:
Happy Wednesday, everyone! I am on the search for a Santa for this years Christmas at the Farm at The Hayloft

Casting breakdown:

"Christmas at the Farm," an immersive Santa's Grotto filled to the brim with excitement and adventure. Synopsis: Families join the Santa's crazy elves to learn the magic of an elf, help them make the reindeer food, and know why they feed their reindeer things like magic beans! They then join Santa, Mrs. Claus, and Elf Mittens for the short play before getting a professional photograph and being given a special gift by Mrs Claus. Oh! And there may be some pesky penguins about to cause extra mischief!

Santa 40+: The big man himself! Christmas cheer and joy, a man dedicated to bringing joy and peace to all. A bit of a goofball at times and adores his wife, elves and those pesky penguins. A joyous male-identifying actor to join the team for this year's Christmas celebrations. Ideally, the actor will have a real beard.

Dates: Rehearsals Nov. 21st, 22nd, and 23rd at the studio just outside of Liverpool City Centre. Show runs Dec. 6th, 7th, 13th, 14th, 20th, 21st, 22nd, 23rd,24th (early finish on 24; potential Dec. 18-19) at The Hayloft in Sandy Lane, Bold Heath, Great Sankey, Widnes, England

Pay: Rehearsals are paid at National Living Wage

Show days: ¬£20.00 per hour, average of 8.5 hours a day.

Self Employed basis, we understand Christmas is a busy and can be an expensive time so we strive to have a very quick pay window so no one is waiting for wages over the Christmas period.

We are on the hunt for some elves, so if this interests you, please email me, and I can send you the details.

 

Please send CV/Spotlight or any questions to: erinhayloftevents@gmail.com

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I‚Äôve been training with Steve Eastin and it‚Äôs honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You‚Äôve seen this guy, he‚Äôs in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he‚Äôs teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just‚Ä¶ different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It‚Äôs not gonna be for everyone but if you‚Äôre someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you‚Äôre just along for the ride, this is that.

It‚Äôs rooted in Charles Conrad‚Äôs whole ‚Äúchoiceless awareness‚Äù thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure ‚Äúbeats‚Äù land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you‚Äôre curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything‚Äôs filmed so you‚Äôre used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They‚Äôre small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn‚Äôt still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it‚Äôs a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

items.text:
SHOWCASE
Wow. What a day!

This lot were absolutely RUDDY MAGNIFICENT yesterday ‚Äî they completely smashed it out of the park. Not only did they give fantastic performances, but the teamwork, support, and camaraderie between them all was just incredible. I‚Äôm beyond proud of every single one of them.

A huge thank you to everyone who came along to watch ‚Äî from family and friends to members of the public and industry professionals. It was such a joy to hear all the fabulous feedback and to know how much everyone enjoyed the afternoon.

A special mention to Luna and Opal, who joined us as part of the production ‚Äî two little stars who were fabulous and so professional.

We also had a bit of a Line of Duty reunion, with Bridgerton‚Äôs @claudia__jessie (Line of Duty series 4) and @gregssspiper (Line of Duty series 1, 4 & 5) coming along to support ‚Äî such a treat to see them both!

And it was a real honour to have the wonderful Colin Edwards there with us too ‚Äî my former drama teacher from ITV Workshop, and the inspirational person our scholarship is named after. Having him in the audience made the day even more special.

Finally, a heartfelt thank you for the incredible flowers, gifts, and card ‚Äî I‚Äôm truly humbled. It‚Äôs such a privilege to work with such talented, kind, and generous people.

And a big shoutout to my lovely friend @corrangreen, who couldn‚Äôt be there but sent beautiful flowers to let me know she was thinking of us. A very special human ‚ù§Ô∏è

#theworkshopactorsstudio #theworkshop #birmingham #actingclass #showcase #actors #bridgerton #lineofduty #itvworkshop #colinedwards

We‚Äôre on the lookout for some frightfully fun volunteers (or ghoulish gig-seekers!) to join us for our Halloween Spooky Walk at Trafford Waters Care Home on Thursday, 31st October at 5pm! üïî

We're inviting anyone who loves Halloween and has a flair for the dramatic to be part of our spooky trail ‚Äî just bring your own costume, makeup, and a good dose of spooky spirit!

‚ú® What you need to do:

Dress up in your best Halloween costume

Do your own makeup (creepy or kooky!)

Be ready to jump out and give our guests a little scare!

Be mindful that the event is open to the public, including children and older adults ‚Äî so keep the scares fun, not frightening.

üí∏ This can be a paid role, or you‚Äôre welcome to volunteer ‚Äî it‚Äôs entirely up to you!

üìç Location: Trafford Waters Care Home

üïî Time: 5:00 PM

üìÖ Date: Friday, 31st October

Interested in joining our spooky crew? Drop us a message or leave a comment below! Let‚Äôs make this Halloween one to remember! ü¶áüíÄ

#HalloweenAtTraffordWaters #SpookyWalk #TraffordEvents #Halloween2025 #JoinTheScare

# üåπ Master Social Media Post ‚Äì IGNITE THE ROMANCE (Extended)

‚ù§Ô∏è IGNITE THE ROMANCE ‚ù§Ô∏è
This photobook was more than a shoot ‚Äì it was an emotional journey.

From the very first click of the camera, something shifted. The rain scenes weren‚Äôt just staged drama ‚Äì the cold drops, the closeness of two people, the intensity of eye contact created a palpable electricity on set.

Between takes, there were moments of shared laughter, moments of quiet vulnerability, and an unspoken understanding: this wasn‚Äôt about pretending to be in love, but about channeling real human intimacy.

‚ú® Highlights of the shoot:

From the very first moment, the atmosphere shifted. The rain scenes weren‚Äôt just about water falling on fabric ‚Äì they were about two people breathing in sync, skin chilled by the storm, eyes locked, hearts racing. The set went quiet, as if everyone was holding their breath with us.

Between takes, there was laughter, shared warmth, and a surprising tenderness. One moment, passion burned hot; the next, there was a fragile silence that made the chemistry even more powerful. These weren‚Äôt staged emotions ‚Äì they were lived in the moment.

üéØ The goal of IGNITE THE ROMANCE:
To prove that I, Dan Martin Roesch, can embody the romantic leading man ‚Äì not just through looks, but through real connection, vulnerability, and emotional depth.

üåç Shared with my international film and casting community.

ü§ù Proudly professionally represented, ready for productions worldwide.

üîó IMDb: https://www.imdb.com/de/name/nm6401783/

üé≠ FREE Introductory DRAMA Workshop For Young People In MANCHESTER This NOVEMBER üé≠

Join us at Red Players Academy for the FREE LAUNCH WORKSHOP of our BRAND NEW SATURDAY CLASS at our well-established and highly reputable drama school for young performers aged 9+

üåê www.redplayersacademy.com/courses

‚Ä¢ Strong work ethic, relentless discipline, and ability to perform under discomfort, pressure, and challenging conditions.

Seeking opportunities in modeling, acting, and performance ‚Äî primarily in the UK (based in London ) but open to international projects. items.text:
CASTING CALL

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production

Project Type: BFA Short Film

Union Status: Non-Union

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected

Shooting Dates: TBD

Shooting Location: Orlando area

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her.

We have not set an exact shoot date, but we plan to begin filming sometime in November. This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production.

Character Breakdowns:

MONOMAY: Female, Late Teens (20s), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

JASON: Male, Late Teens (20s), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma.

FAN CLUB: Any gender, Teens (20s), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

Casting call ¬∑ 04.10 ¬∑ 14:00‚Äì16:00 ¬∑ Krak√≥w

When and where: October 4, 14:00‚Äì16:00, Krak√≥w, Romanowicza 19b. 

The project: student independent short film, prepared for submission to European festivals and media exposure.
Plot: action takes place 30 years from our time; a dystopia about the "oppression" of the body and rebellion against a repressive regime.

items.text:
CASTING CALL - PRESENTER FOR SOCIAL MEDIA CAMPAIGN FOR FINANCIAL SERVICES COMPANY IN LONDON (POTENTIALLY 13th OCTOBER)

Hi all, we‚Äôre currently casting for a presenter for a short social media video with us. We‚Äôre looking for someone with experience presenting, who can share links for us to review.

We‚Äôre hoping for someone with bags of personality who‚Äôs happy and confident to approach people in the street and stoke up a conversation, but you‚Äôll also be required to deliver a piece to camera. You‚Äôd need to be very confident riding a bike and have a decent level of fitness, as we‚Äôll be following you cycle around London for a couple of hours on a branded bike.

Please only send on details if you have Presenting experience, with links to recent work. Email details to casting@feral-films.com. Please do not DM me, only send details via email.

This is a paid role, with travel (to and from the location within London) and sustenance all covered on the shoot.

The shoot date is pencilled for the 13th October, this may change however. The location is likely to be Central London. 

Thank you!

Gulliver‚Äôs Theme Park Resorts are on the talent hunt for talented individuals to join our thrilling and magical experiences!  Fright Fiesta Halloween & Festive Christmas Casting Opportunities.

CASTING FOR: DANCERS, SCARE ACTORS, STREET THEATRE ENTERTAINERS, ELVES AND STAGE PRESENTERS

OPEN AUDITION, GULLIVER'S WORLD, WARRINGTON

SATURDAY 27TH SEPTEMBER, Gulliver's World Resort Hotel, Shackleton Close, Warrington, WA5 9YZ.  Registration at 17.30pm.  

Report to the hotel reception with your CV.  Please come with suitable attire to dance.  Free car parking available on site.  If you cannot make the audition date but are interested in winter opportunities, please email Casting with your CV.

Scare Actors: Bring our family scare attractions to life by delivering spine-tingling thrills and fun.

Street Theatre Entertainers: Delivering spooky fun and festive cheer, captivating guests with your improvisation and character creation skills. If you have any circus skills or stilt experience this would advantageous. 

Dancers: Shine in our daytime and evening shows for Halloween & Christmas

Actors & Puppeteers: Animate our stage shows and immersive experiences, making stories come alive with your performance

Elves: Create unforgettable moments in our grotto experience, spreading holiday joy as Santa‚Äôs helpers.

Santa: To bring alive the Christmas cheer in our grottos making a magical experience for the whole family.  Rates up to ¬£20 per hour.

Contracts Available from Late September to 1st January 2026 with flexible working hours. If you are interested in opportunities at Gulliver's Valley, Rotherham, Gulliver's Land Milton Keynes please email your CV highlighting which Resort you are interest in.

casting@gulliversfun.co.uk

items.text:
Gm, wanted to invite all to a great Casting Call Happening October 18th!! More information below! Please comment below if you can come! W Talent NYC would love to see you there!..

DEAR INVITED TALENT, 

We would like to invite you to our NEXT OPEN CALL session on SATURDAY, OCTOBER 18th, 3PM (SHARP) at 447 West 36th Street, New York, NY.
* The HUDSON YARDS LOFT. STUDIO 4. 

PLEASE ARRIVE AT 2:30PM TO REGISTER.

We are currently CASTING for ZARA kids, THE GAP kids, and multiple TV/Film projects for NETFLIX (Non-Union) as well as Fashion Weeks in the following Countries:
New York Fashion Week:  February 12 - 17, 2026 in NYC. 
Depending on the Project, Payrate will vary:

ADULT PAY RATE: $1000/day - $8000/day (18+)
TEEN PAY RATE: $1000/day - $5000/day (13 - 17)
CHILDREN PAY RATE: $800/day - $2500/day (ages 2 - 12)

MUST BRING A PRINTED OUT PHOTO (8x10) simple snapshot/selfie, OR Acting Headshot/Resume, OR YOUR MODEL COMPOSITE CARD.  Any of these are fine.

Please respond to this message to confirm your attendance with "Will be attending". 

Please keep this DATE/TIME/LOCATION on your calendar. We do NOT send out reminders. 

Open Calls will last approximately 1.5 hour.

Actors - Please have a 60 second monologue to perform. No swearing. No political,  No sexual, or religious content, please. 

Female Models - Please wear heels to perform a videotaped Runway Walk and wear a form-fitting all black outfit.

Male Models - Please wear jeans and a form-fitting t-shirt.

Children: Please wear casual/comfortable outfits.

We're casting for our magical Christmas Grotto experience in the Milton Keynes and Bedford area and we‚Äôre on the lookout for a charismatic, professional Mother Christmas to join the team!

üìç Location: 2 venues across MILTON KEYNES & BEDFORD
MK44 3QP & MK17 8UE
üìÜ Contract: December 2025
üí∏ Rate: ¬£20 per hour

‚ú® Requirements:

‚Ä¢ Entry-level acting skills

‚Ä¢ Basic script work and immersive performance ability

‚Ä¢ Confident group singing of children‚Äôs Christmas songs

‚Ä¢ Must absolutely love Christmas!

You‚Äôll be part of a heartwarming festive experience for families and children, in a beautifully themed setting. 

üßù‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è We‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Confident, energetic performers with great improvisation skills

‚Ä¢ Friendly, reliable team players

‚Ä¢ Previous experience working with children or in character-based roles is a plus

üìå Important Info:

‚Ä¢ Costume and full training provided

‚Ä¢ Paid rehearsals and site visits will be scheduled in early November ‚Äì exact dates TBC

‚Ä¢ Below is the confirmed list of working dates and shift times:

Tue, Dec 2 ‚Äì 1:30 PM to 7:00 PM

Thu, Dec 4 ‚Äì 1:30 PM to 6:00 PM

Tue, Dec 9 ‚Äì 10:30 AM to 5:00 PM

Tue, Dec 16 ‚Äì 10:30 AM to 7:00 PM

Fri, Dec 19 ‚Äì 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

Sat, Dec 20 ‚Äì 8:30 AM to 6:00 PM

üì© To apply:
Send your CV, headshot, and any relevant performance footage to: castings@evokeents.com
Subject line: MOTHER CHRISTMAS CONTRACT
Tell us a little about why you‚Äôd be a great fit & the dates you're interested in working ‚Äî we‚Äôd love to hear from you!

Exciting News! Following the incredible success of our award-winning short film 'The Hit' at the Short Film Festival Manchester, Marble Academy and Solefuge Media Productions are thrilled to announce auditions for our upcoming low-budget short film, ‚ÄòHotel Rent,‚Äô set to film early next year.

We're on the lookout for six talented actors to bring this project to life! While these roles are unpaid, we will cover travel expenses and provide meals. 
Plus, this is a fantastic opportunity to enhance your showreel or portfolio!

If you‚Äôre passionate about acting and eager to dive into a vibrant creative environment, we want to hear from you! 
Please send us a direct message or an email to marbleacademy@hotmail.com. Share a bit about yourself, the role that excites you the most, and what draws you to that character.
Auditions are in-person on Saturday, November 22nd, in Swinton, Manchester.

Don‚Äôt forget to include a link to your Spotlight or Backstage profile. We can‚Äôt wait to find the incredible talent that will shine in our project!

Bunny Business Events is casting for two magical roles to join our team this festive season:

‚ú® Elsa ‚Äì The Snow Queen

We‚Äôre looking for a confident, charismatic performer to bring Elsa to life at children‚Äôs parties, Christmas events and seasonal celebrations. Singing ability is a huge bonus (but not essential) ‚Äì what matters most is your ability to engage, enchant and command the room. You‚Äôll make magical memories for children and families, creating unforgettable moments through storytelling, games, photos, and more. This is an ongoing role into 2026 with consistent, frequent weekend work.

üéÖ Santa Claus

We‚Äôre also seeking a warm, jolly performer to step into the iconic red suit this Christmas! As Santa, you‚Äôll spread festive cheer, meet and greet families and deliver magical experiences at grottos, parties and corporate events. Age-appropriate appearance for the role is required.

üí∞ Pay: ¬£30 ‚Äì ¬£50 per hour (depending on event and experience)

üìÖ When: Frequent and flexible work across weekends, school holidays and the run-up to Christmas

üìç Where: Events across Greater Manchester, South Manchester, Cheshire, and Warrington ‚Äì you must live within comfortable travelling distance of SK9 postcode

üåü We‚Äôre Looking For:

Confident, fun, and engaging performers who can command a room

Strong with children and families ‚Äì warm, approachable and full of energy

Experience in performing arts, acting or entertainment is advantageous

Must drive and have your own transport (travel costs subsidised)

Weekend and festive season availability is essential

üéÅ What We Offer:

All costume, props, and training provided

Flexible, frequent bookings with excellent pay

A fun, rewarding opportunity to bring joy and magic to children during the most wonderful time of the year

üì© How to Apply:

Send your CV and a recent headshot to hello@bunnybusinessevents.co.uk

üì± Follow us on social media: Bunny Business Events

Artistic Proposal ‚Äì C√≠a. B√°scula
Show: "Jumping Stars"ÔøΩDiscipline: Korean Teeterboard

Company Introduction
We are C√≠a. B√°scula, a contemporary circus company specializing in Korean teeterboard, composed of artists trained at the National University of San Mart√≠n (Argentina). Our work blends high-level acrobatics with a contemporary stage language, adaptable to diverse contexts and audiences.
We would love the opportunity to present our show "Jumping Stars" as part of your circus show.

Technical Requirements ‚Äì Rider for "Jumping Stars"
Stage Space Requirements:
* Minimum dimensions: 3 meters (width) x 6 meters (depth)
* Minimum height clearance: 6 meters
* Surface: flat and stable, with at least 1 m¬≤ of level ground to install the teeterboard system. If the ground is uneven, it is sufficient to level the area where the board will be placed.
Teeterboard Specifications:
* Dimensions: 3.15 meters long x 45 cm wide
* Material: hard, flexible wood (preferably Guatamb√∫, Brazilian Lapacho, or French Ash)
Lighting:
* Minimum requirement: general lighting, adaptable for both indoor and outdoor settings
* Colored lights may be used ‚Äì no complex lighting design is necessary
Sound:
* The company provides 3 audio tracks for the performance
* Requirements:
    * At least 2 speakers or amplifiers (200W minimum)
    * 1 sound technician to play the tracks according to our cues
Setup and Takedown:
* Setup time: approx. 15 minutes (on the day of the performance)
* Takedown and loading: approx. 15 minutes after the show
Loading and Unloading:
* The company will handle loading and unloading of its equipment
* It is essential that the transport vehicle can access the performance area as closely as possible

Video Material
https://youtu.be/-AKUqShvQUs?si=wweW-faS-UAPChNf

Social Media
* Instagram:ÔøΩ@cia.basculaÔøΩ@acrobate.arÔøΩ@lauguatojpÔøΩ@morenieves_

items.text:
Gulliver‚Äôs Theme Park Resorts are on the talent hunt for talented individuals to join our thrilling and magical experiences!  Fright Fiesta Halloween & Festive Christmas Casting Opportunities.

CASTING FOR: DANCERS, SCARE ACTORS, STREET THEATRE ENTERTAINERS, ELVES AND STAGE PRESENTERS

OPEN AUDITION, GULLIVER'S WORLD, WARRINGTON

SATURDAY 27TH SEPTEMBER, Gulliver's World Resort Hotel, Shackleton Close, Warrington, WA5 9YZ.  Registration at 17.30pm.  

Report to the hotel reception with your CV.  Please come with suitable attire to dance.  Free car parking available on site.  If you cannot make the audition date but are interested in winter opportunities, please email Casting with your CV.

Scare Actors: Bring our family scare attractions to life by delivering spine-tingling thrills and fun.

Street Theatre Entertainers: Delivering spooky fun and festive cheer, captivating guests with your improvisation and character creation skills. If you have any circus skills or stilt experience this would advantageous. 

Dancers: Shine in our daytime and evening shows for Halloween & Christmas

Actors & Puppeteers: Animate our stage shows and immersive experiences, making stories come alive with your performance

Elves: Create unforgettable moments in our grotto experience, spreading holiday joy as Santa‚Äôs helpers.

Santa: To bring alive the Christmas cheer in our grottos making a magical experience for the whole family.  Rates up to ¬£20 per hour.

Contracts Available from Late September to 1st January 2026 with flexible working hours. If you are interested in opportunities at Gulliver's Valley, Rotherham, Gulliver's Land Milton Keynes please email your CV highlighting which Resort you are interest in.

casting@gulliversfun.co.uk

items.text: Looking for acting jobs in and around Liverpool i Would like to start a career in acting

topComments.text:
Do you have training? Headshots? Showreel? On Spotlight? 
A Director I know had 5300 applications via Spotlight for a short film she‚Äôs making. There are so many talented people but so many talented, trained people with a fab range of headshots who are struggling to get auditions. That‚Äôs not to say it‚Äôs impossible but start with training, apply to agencies, do some am-dram, get together some showreels to show CDs what you can do. Follow CD instagrams so you know when they are looking for your casting type. You obviously can‚Äôt just start a career but with years of work doing the above you will hopefully get seen. Good luck.
You gotta look out for casting calls, unless you are an a lister, nobody comes to you, you have to find them.

üö®CASTING ACTORS for a dark arthouse short film "Dollface"üö®

Date :2-3 days between Oct 22nd-28th.

Location: Los Angeles CA

Rate: Non union, Low budget and unpaid. Here is what I can offer!

Full film credit , Reel material, Festival submissions, Super cool vibe with a cool, dark storyüòé

Project: This is a passion project of mine. The film explores the dark underbelly of hustler sexwork.  When one of two best friends goes missing after a night of working, a male hustler seeks revenge on the person who took his friend's life. It is dark and provocative and pushes boundaries.

 

Roles: 

Francesca (Principal Female 20s)- She is bold and confident, bit of a firecracker, reckless. (Must be comfortable with smoking a prop cigarette and wearing semi revealing clothes as she is in the sexwork industry)

John (Principal 27-30s)  - Stone cold. Blunt. Sleezy. He picks up a male sex worker and takes him to a motel in exchange for a good night. (Must be comfortable being semi nude, and doing simulated sexual activities. NO SEX SCENES)

Murderer (Principal 25-37)- Seemingly normal. Respectful and friendly but it's all a facade. He picks up hustlers and is responsible for their brutal fate. 

Please ask me if you have any questions! If actors would like, intimacy coordinator will be present. 

Casting from self tapes! Please email me with a headshot, resume and reel (if applicable) to marcoroni2003@gmail.com

items.text:
My name is Adelola Mary Haastrup, and I‚Äôm a passionate actress currently based in Nigeria. I‚Äôm looking to expand my career in the UK and am actively seeking opportunities for visa sponsorship.

I started acting at the age of 7, performing in stage productions. While much of my early work was in gospel theater, I‚Äôm not particularly religious, and my focus has always been on the craft of acting. I‚Äôm eager to explore a wide range of roles in film, TV, theater, and commercial work, and I‚Äôm excited to branch out into new genres and experiences.

In addition to my acting experience, I studied Music Technology with a major in Stage Performing Arts for 2 years , and I have full documentation of all my final projects from that time. This technical training complements my stage performance and has given me a comprehensive understanding of both the artistic and technical sides of the industry.

I was also part of a gospel drama group form 2011 to 2020 , where I won 4 "Card Awards," including Best Actress  (twice), Best Dressed, and Best Minister. These awards reflect my dedication to the craft, and I‚Äôm incredibly proud of them.

I‚Äôm looking forward to collaborating on a wide range of acting roles in the UK‚Äôs vibrant and inclusive creative industry, and I‚Äôm actively seeking potential employers who are willing to support visa sponsorships for skilled performers like me.

If you have any leads or know of any production companies, agents, or casting opportunities, I would love to hear from you! Please feel free to DM me or comment below.

Thank you so much for your time and consideration. I look forward to connecting with you all!

Need a bit of a spooky promo shoot for your brand? Send me your stuff! I'll get it sorted üòÅ üéÉü¶äüçÅ

Need some updated headshots? Pop along to the studio and I'll be with you every step of the way! I love building up your confidence and taking you from being terrified to terrific! Honestly I've been told many times from many customers that I have a knack for bringing out the best in people and making them feel good about themselves - so you are in very safe hands! 

Got a spooky themed show coming up and need a quick Halloween promo shoot? Let's gather round the cauldron and cook up a plan üéÉ 

Need some spooky scary stop motion for your little business?? Get in touch and we'll make a spooky story board! 

Don't be afraid to ask for a quote - I like to think I price fairly and prefer to do a sliding scale for different sized businesses. In the north east I'm very aware things can be tough for creatives! I also am a tiny business myself and put my heart and soul into everything I do, so please do not be afraid to ask!

Hey everyone! 
We‚Äôre looking for **4 people who‚Äôd like to act** in a **camera and directing exercise** at our film school.
No previous experience needed, just enthusiasm and a willingness to collaborate.

**What it‚Äôs about:**
We‚Äôll be working on **short dialogue scenes**, each focused on **a specific emotion**. The exercise will explore **camera movement** and how actors and directors adapt to each other, just like in a film, but with short and experimental scenes.

A HUGE thank you to everyone who has taken the time to apply, we‚Äôve smashed the number of applicants we‚Äôve had previously which is amazing! üò±
We‚Äôve highlighted the key points to note:

üìå We‚Äôre a small agency and are incredibly busy at the moment, we appreciate people want to know but we cannot give updates throughout the screening process and replying to emails asking for information stops us being able to process applications

üìå If you have applied during the book opening period you will be notified whether successful or not but please bear with us as we work through applications

üìå Our social team have NO access to any information
regarding applications

üìå Our in person assessment day will be Sunday 19th October for successful applicants

üìå We will post on socials once we have contacted all applicants

üìå Also to clarify, you don‚Äôt get a confirmation email when you completed the application, if you were able to submit, it will have gone through. üôÇ

And again thank you to everyone who took the time to apply we‚Äôve got our fingers crossed for you all!
#thedramamob

message.text:
HALLOWEEN CARNIVAL REHEARSALS 
üìç African Caribbean Centre
üóìÔ∏è Tuesdays, 6PM

We have always known that there is power in our movement. That our ancestors held on to something special!. We never just danced, or drummed, or sang, we commanded the elements! The  universe  submitted to our presence. We affected  cosmologies through our movement. 
They still don't understand how we did it., how carried magic and power through our movement.

Our classes are journey to commune with our heritage.
Together with Katumba, the Merseyside International Centre for Caribbean Carnival and Black Imagination are delivering a powerful Halloween experience. drum, dance, and ancestral Mas fused into living ritual. To be performed on the streets for the Halloween Parade.

REHEARSALS 
üìç African Caribbean Centre
üóìÔ∏è Tuesdays, 6PM

Step into the circle. Claim your culture!

items.title: NAGRANIA SZUKAMY:

items.text:
Agencja Adliner Sp. z o.o. poszukuje lektor√≥w - dzieci do animacji edukacyjnej 

Szczeg√≥≈Çy: 
- nagranie w Warszawie prawdopodobnie pod koniec przysz≈Çego tygodnia  
- lokalizacja nagrania - sadyba
- czas nagrania 2-3h 
- wynagrodzenie 500z≈Ç netto na Umowƒô o Dzie≈Ço (z przekazaniem praw bez ogranicze≈Ñ czasowych na wszystkich polach eksploatacji) Jest to pierwsze z planowanej serii nagra≈Ñ, wiƒôc jest mo≈ºliwa kontynuacja wsp√≥≈Çpracy 
- poszukujemy: 2 g≈Ços√≥w ch≈Çopc√≥w i 3 g≈Ços√≥w dziewczynek, w wieku 8 -13 lat 
- tematem nagrania jest ochrona ≈õrodowiska, segregacja odpad√≥w i recykling. W wyniku nagrania powstanƒÖ trzy kr√≥tkie animacje edukacyjne, kt√≥re zostanƒÖ u≈ºyte w materia≈Çach programu edukacyjnego kierowanego do szk√≥≈Ç podstawowych.  

W celu zg≈Çoszenia prosimy i wys≈Çanie pr√≥bki g≈Çosu (nagranie telefonem) odczytujƒÖcej poni≈ºszy tekst (odpowiednio dla ch≈Çopc√≥w i dla dziewczynek) na adres: [praca@adliner.pl](mailto:praca@adliner.pl) 
W tytule prosimy podaƒá: "G≈Ços ch≈Çopca/ dziewczynki do animacji edukacyjnej" a w zg≈Çoszeniu prosimy o podanie danych kontaktowych rodzica (telefon kom√≥rkowy) 
Na zg≈Çoszenia czekamy do 5 pa≈∫dziernika 

Tekst dla Ch≈Çopc√≥w 
Dzieci sƒÖ w fabryce papieru, Janek spoglƒÖda na du≈ºe bele z papierem i m√≥wi: WyglƒÖdajƒÖ jak zwiniƒôte latajƒÖce dywany! Ka≈ºdy papier ma taki kolor? Niebieski pojemnik jest poczƒÖtkiem drogi prowadzƒÖcej do prawdziwych skarb√≥w!

Tekst dla dziewczynek

AMERIVENTS is Hiring!

We‚Äôre excited to assemble our Dream Team of talented professionals for iconic NYC events like SNL wrap parties, movie premieres, and sporting events.

**Building Our Dream Team**

At Amerivents, we are committed to assembling and empowering a "Dream Team" of talented individuals who bring diverse skills, shared values, and a unified purpose to every endeavor. Much like a championship sports team, we believe that our collective success is built on the strength and collaboration of our team members, each contributing their unique expertise to achieve exceptional results.

**Now Hiring FRONT OF HOUSE:**
* Catering Hospitality Staff
* Servers
* Bartenders
* Captains

**Now Hiring BACK OF HOUSE:**
* Dishwasher
* Utility
* Grill Cook
* Line Cook

**Requirements:**

2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience

You must be 18 or older

**Next Steps:**
1. Complete the interview survey here: [https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8](https://forms.gle/r3B2ib3kssxRfF5v8)
2. Visit[ www.amerivents.com](http://www.amerivents.com/) and click ‚ÄúApply‚Äù (mention ‚ÄúCORE-NYC‚Äù in the referral box).

**Why Amerivents?**
* Fast-paced, exciting, and team-oriented work environment
* Flexible schedules‚Äîyou choose your availability!
* Gain unforgettable experiences in the hospitality industry
* Experience unique and inspiring event locations!

**What We‚Äôre Looking For:**
* 2+ years of catering or high-end retail experience
* Professional, adaptable, and radiate positivity team players
* Composure under pressure and ability to adapt to dynamic environments
* Flexible and reliable team players who can seamlessly adjust to varying roles and tasks
* Ability to lift 50 lbs and stand for extended periods

**To Our Team:**
We offer the chance to pursue your passions while contributing to a company that values your unique talents and provides the support you need to excel.

We look forward to hearing from you!

**This is not an official job offer**

items.text:
CASTING CALL

Production Company: GreenHouse Films Production

Project Type: BFA Short Film

Union Status: Non-Union

Pay Status: Unpaid Projected

Shooting Dates: TBD

Shooting Location: Orlando area

Summary: A lonely girl shunned by her school finds comfort in plants and in the one friend who truly sees her.

We have not set an exact shoot date, but we plan to begin filming sometime in November. This is an unpaid project - copy and credit will be given to all involved. This is a non-union production.

Character Breakdowns:

MONOMAY: Female, Late Teens (20s), A teen girl marked by facial scars and iris coloboma, finds purpose and comfort in tending to her beloved plants.

JASON: Male, Late Teens (20s), The school's "Golden Boy" athlete, hides his insecurities behind charisma.

FAN CLUB: Any gender, Teens (20s), A group of students that fawn over Jason and seek his attention.

How to Submit: Please send an email to greenhousefilmsproduction@gmail.com to reserve a time slot for auditions.

So proud to be the Executive Producer and Casting Director on Taro O'Halloran‚Äôs Short Horror Film  HUMANZEE starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton as Ziggy!! 

It is screening at Screamfest Horror Film Festival in Hollywood at Mann‚Äôs Chinese Theatre!

sharedPost.text:
Congratulations to Taro O'Halloran of Weymouth High School Class of 2020 on the screening of his Short Horror Film Humanzee starring Liz Bishop, Cheryl Pynn and introducing Zach Norton of Weymouth at Screamfest Horror Film Festival at the @TCL Chinese Theater in Hollywood!  

I am so honored to have the titles of Executive Producer and Casting Director on this film!

The hope is someone will see it and want to develop it into a Full Length Feature Film!

I see this film bringing home some awards!

My fingers are crossed for Taro‚Äôs Team!

Thank you Diane Purdy's Children's Theatre Workshop for giving me my own Stage from 9 to 49 and for letting me pass it on to John and Jake who brought Taro home from school one day and we all collaborated on multiple video productions with Diane‚Äôs costumes for years!

sharedPost.text:
Casting Call

Production: Mother's Ruin, by Steve Bird (Back by popular demand!)

The story so far in the life of Liverpool comedian Garry Skyner, one of Britain's first- born victims of the Thalidomide medical disaster. Steve Birds play is a moving and emotional, yet hard hitting play about the highs, lows, struggles and sheer determination of a loving Mother and her son who refused to be beaten by the Government and company that profited from this medical disaster.

We are looking for a talented female actor playing range 20-30ys, who is from Liverpool or can do a convincing accent, for the lead role of Frances, Gary's Mum.
Frances is a spirited, humourous woman, who whilst having a heart of gold, has an inner strength, is tough, and fights for her child and what is right.
If you believe you are what we are looking for please send you CV and headshot to elainestewart46@yahoo.com 

Auditions to take place on Sunday 21st September 1pm-3pm at a Liverpool venue to be disclosed on receipt of CV, and a script will be provided. 

Performances will take place at the Epstein Theatre on 27th and 28th February 2026.

You must be available for rehearsals Sundays 1pm- 4pm (in Liverpool) starting 2nd November.
*This is a profit share production

. Filming the event (reactions) on a phone (2 people required)

. Something different to talk about (and looks great on a CV for anyone in events, film, or theatre)

If you're free, reliable, and up for being part of something mysterious and fun, drop me a message here or comment below and I'll share the details.

Thanks! 

Charlie

**CASTING CALL ‚Äî BL REALITY DATING SERIES (PAID)**

**Synopsis:**

Six gay men spend one day together under the same roof, exploring love and identity through every colour of the rainbow! 

Inspired by the six colours of Pride (life, healing, sunlight, nature, serenity and spirit), will the boys find a spark or something real along the way?

**What we‚Äôre looking for:**

Singapore-based gay men (18+) who are

üåàComfortable being yourself on camera

üåàOpen to meeting new people, sharing your thoughts

üåàDown to have fun and be part of something authentic

üåàDifferent looks, backgrounds, and personalities welcome ‚Äî come as you are!

**Interested? Reach out to us at casting@250films.co by 30 Nov 2025 with:**

üåàName

üåàAge

üåàRecent photos/headshots

Bottle Girls üçæ
I'm looking for 6 confident and curvy bottle girls to join our team for a 3 month contract running from early November to the end of January.

Details:
 ‚Ä¢ Location: Lagos, Nigeria
 ‚Ä¢ Return flights and accommodation will be provided
 ‚Ä¢ Must be available to start in early November
 ‚Ä¢ Must have a curvy figure and a fun, outgoing personality

If you‚Äôre interested, please send me a direct message including:
 1. Your current location
 2. Recent photos (to be shared with the client for selection)

It‚Äôs a great short-term opportunity to be part of an exciting venue and event season in Lagos!

items.text:
ARE YOU AN ACTOR STUCK IN YOUR HEAD???

Yep... same. But I‚Äôve been training with Steve Eastin and it‚Äôs honestly flipping everything upside down for me. You‚Äôve seen this guy, he‚Äôs in like 200 movies [Catch Me If You Can, Con Air, Field of Dreams, Matchstick Men, etc.].

Not a lot of people even realize he‚Äôs teaching again. Feels like some random secret I lucked into.

What he does is just‚Ä¶ different. Really different. Not about analyzing or breaking stuff down. It‚Äôs not gonna be for everyone but if you‚Äôre someone like me who gets trapped in overthinking, this is the kind of work that yanks you out of your head and dumps you right into the moment. If you live for those times where it feels like something else is taking over and you‚Äôre just along for the ride, this is that.

It‚Äôs rooted in Charles Conrad‚Äôs whole ‚Äúchoiceless awareness‚Äù thing. Basically stripping your brain of anything to hang onto and forcing you to just respond. No scene breakdowns, no making sure ‚Äúbeats‚Äù land. Just keeping it alive and messy and letting the work happen through you. If you‚Äôre curious, this article explains it better:

[[https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/](https://www.backstage.com/.../article/something-think-64356/)](https://www.backstage.com/magazine/article/something-think-64356/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Class is super bare bones. Sit across, cold read, memorize, toss it, repeat. Just working the muscle of not thinking. Everything‚Äôs filmed so you‚Äôre used to being on camera too.

And the wild part, Conrad literally handpicked Steve to carry this forward. He taught for decades, everyone in casting knew his people, then he retired. And now he just randomly opened these tiny classes at his house. They‚Äôre small, intimate, and honestly feel like something that shouldn‚Äôt still exist.

If this even slightly calls to you, it‚Äôs a rare shot.

Classes here:

[[https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/)](https://www.officialsteveeastin.com/?fbclid=IwZXh0bgNhZW0CMTAAYnJpZBExM2s0WGxFWTdncEhJTmxocgEeCVIM5HcT1y_cwi-yFme2XrGgrFIf-1zB9ic_Hs8B6I0eQe1Dy_6RVHYQfBM_aem_ZtitTlgW3beKBmQOc9GAQQ)

Most recently, she appears as Rachel in Amazon Prime‚Äôs Top 10* *show* The Runarounds*.
